720698f-a.text:
(1) John Street, south side, west from (No. 48) but not including
William Street to but not including Broadway, showing in the foreground the John Street N.E. Church (No. 44-46). Intersection shown on the right is Nassau Street. The original edifice was erected on this site in 1768, and rebuilt in 1817. The present building being erected in 1841.
May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) A limited view, showing Nos. 48, 46-44 (church), 42, and a part of
38-36. This view is as seen from Dutch Street.
May 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) John Street,South Side,between Nassau and William Streets,showing  the John Street Methodist Episcopal Church.
